89
00:11:30,771 --> 00:11:34,743
I think snoring
can be quite charming, actually.

90
00:11:35,172 --> 00:11:37,220
This way.

91
00:11:37,332 --> 00:11:41,382
Why do they call it a thunder box?
Cos it's out in the wind and rain?

92
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:45,054
I suppose. But you always need
to keep your shoes on.

93
00:11:45,173 --> 00:11:50,179
- Are there stinging nettles?
- Yes, and scorpions and centipedes.

94
00:11:50,293 --> 00:11:51,534
Hell.

95
00:11:51,654 --> 00:11:54,385
- Can you swim?
- Not very well.

96
00:11:55,894 --> 00:11:59,820
I'll wake you up. There's
a swimming hole we go to every day.

97
00:11:59,935 --> 00:12:03,223
- I'm Sheela.
- Estella.

98
00:12:06,056 --> 00:12:09,299
Does he always take the Bible
with him to the dunny?

99
00:12:09,416 --> 00:12:13,216
It wasn't the Bible. He just doesn't
like wasting time, that's all.

100
00:12:16,257 --> 00:12:20,307
Well, from the size of it,
he could be there all night.

101
00:12:22,537 --> 00:12:25,621
I should've warned him
about the redbacks.

102
00:12:25,738 --> 00:12:28,787
- What are they?
- Small spiders with big teeth.

103
00:12:28,898 --> 00:12:32,745
- They live under toilet seats.
- How do you know if they're there?

104
00:12:32,859 --> 00:12:34,782
By the screams.

105
00:13:05,743 --> 00:13:08,030
Ah, there you are.

106
00:13:08,903 --> 00:13:10,951
Mr Lindsay's wonderful, isn't he?

107
00:13:11,063 --> 00:13:13,350
He said we're gonna do
The Sirens next.

108
00:13:13,463 --> 00:13:15,432
- Do you know about them?
- Certainly.

109
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:19,027
They lived on the island of Atlantis
and sang songs from the cliffs

110
00:13:19,145 --> 00:13:22,991
and sailors from passing ships were
driven mad by these gorgeous voices.

111
00:13:23,105 --> 00:13:25,949
And the ships would be dashed
against the rocks

112
00:13:26,066 --> 00:13:28,876
and the sailors dragged down
to a blissful death

113
00:13:28,986 --> 00:13:33,036
with the voices of the sirens
ringing in their ears.

114
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:36,196
I think myths
are a bit stupid, really.

115
00:13:37,147 --> 00:13:39,070
I'll be wearing this.

116
00:13:40,427 --> 00:13:42,714
You know, you could pose, too,
if you like.

117
00:13:42,827 --> 00:13:46,230
He always needs more models.
Go on, try it. Please.

118
00:13:46,348 --> 00:13:48,589
There's some male ones too.

119
00:13:48,708 --> 00:13:50,552
I don't think that's quite for us.

120
00:13:50,669 --> 00:13:54,230
Well, you could always wear a dagger,
strategically placed.

121
00:13:57,109 --> 00:14:02,640
Or a sword. Whichever you need.
And dinner's ready.

122
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:04,832
Oh, that's right.

123
00:14:04,951 --> 00:14:06,918
I was sent to fetch you.

124
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:12,995
I don't...like people thinking
I'm like the other models.

125
00:14:13,111 --> 00:14:16,638
I'm working here as a maid.
Mr Lindsay asked me to pose

126
00:14:16,751 --> 00:14:20,154
and I said I would
if I could keep my clothes on.

127
00:14:20,272 --> 00:14:24,243
Because I really think it's important
to keep one's mystique,

128
00:14:24,353 --> 00:14:26,639
don't you, Mr Campion?

129
00:14:26,753 --> 00:14:29,757
Is it Mr Campion
or Father Anthony?

130
00:14:29,873 --> 00:14:31,443
It's, uh, it's Tony.

131
00:14:33,313 --> 00:14:37,080
Do you think it's a sin...Tony?

132
00:14:37,194 --> 00:14:40,198
I don't think there's anything sinful
about the body.

133
00:14:40,314 --> 00:14:43,762
There's a tradition of religious
painting featuring the nude.

134
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:48,598
It's a question of...how the artist
uses the body that's important.

135
00:14:48,716 --> 00:14:52,766
So, do you think
Mr Lindsay's paintings are rude?

136
00:14:57,077 --> 00:14:59,000
