for your hospitality.

714
01:13:42,032 --> 01:13:43,443
Bottoms up.

715
01:13:43,552 --> 01:13:45,759
We've enjoyed ourselves.

716
01:13:45,873 --> 01:13:48,877
I like a little opposition.
It clears the mind.

717
01:13:56,154 --> 01:14:00,796
So, um, I gather
you're a boxer, Mr Devlin.

718
01:14:00,914 --> 01:14:03,805
Yes, I used to do a bit
of boxing myself, actually.

719
01:14:03,914 --> 01:14:06,236
Quite a keen pugilist in one's day.

720
01:14:06,355 --> 01:14:11,486
Lost a huge part of this tooth from
a great haymaker someone gave me.

721
01:14:11,595 --> 01:14:15,885
I expect you've got some
pretty bad <i>scabs</i> to show as well.

722
01:14:16,876 --> 01:14:22,007
Apart, obviously, from the...
eye thing, which is beastly.

723
01:14:27,118 --> 01:14:29,438
Well, unfortunately,
during his last fight,

724
01:14:29,558 --> 01:14:32,607
Mr Devlin was gasping for air
with his tongue hanging out

725
01:14:32,718 --> 01:14:36,484
and he got this enormous uppercut
under his chin and lost most of it.

726
01:14:36,598 --> 01:14:39,250
Bulldust, Norman.

727
01:14:40,159 --> 01:14:43,049
He makes a brilliant Ulysses, anyhow.

728
01:14:43,159 --> 01:14:46,288
We always call him into the water
and he never comes.

729
01:14:46,399 --> 01:14:48,971
Whoever he was,
you'd try to get him in.

730
01:14:49,080 --> 01:14:53,051
- You'd get in the whole army.
- God, you're charming tonight.

731
01:14:53,160 --> 01:14:57,485
Thinking about the Atlantis series,
I'd like to do more research.

732
01:14:57,601 --> 01:15:00,889
I was thinking of mounting
an expedition to go and find it.

733
01:15:01,001 --> 01:15:03,402
You might like to come.

734
01:15:04,722 --> 01:15:09,047
- Devlin could be the pilot.
- Giddy could be the navigator.

735
01:15:09,722 --> 01:15:11,134
I'm not going if they're going.

736
01:15:11,243 --> 01:15:12,608
- What?
- Why not?

737
01:15:12,723 --> 01:15:14,930
I can't trust you
as far as I could kick you.

738
01:15:15,043 --> 01:15:19,493
- Thanks very much.
- What are you talking about?

739
01:15:19,604 --> 01:15:21,015
You know!

740
01:15:21,124 --> 01:15:24,207
You always eat cheese
when you're feeling guilty.

741
01:15:24,844 --> 01:15:26,256
Excuse me.

742
01:15:29,045 --> 01:15:32,015
Sorry, I'd better go and see
if she's all right.

743
01:15:36,326 --> 01:15:40,218
- What?
- Nothing.

744
01:15:44,366 --> 01:15:46,176
Piglet? You all right?

745
01:15:46,287 --> 01:15:48,654
Yes, I'm...I'm fine, thank you.

746
01:15:50,408 --> 01:15:52,775
Are you feeling a bit funny?

747
01:15:53,888 --> 01:15:55,413
Probably all that Stilton.

748
01:15:57,129 --> 01:16:00,258
You were packing it down,
weren't you?

749
01:16:04,730 --> 01:16:07,620
- Well, I'd better...I'll go back.
- Pooh.

750
01:16:09,650 --> 01:16:12,494
I think...we should talk.

751
01:16:14,331 --> 01:16:20,134
- Right you are. What about?
- Ever since we got here, I...

752
01:16:22,931 --> 01:16:26,254
Well, now, I think some things
are best left unsaid.

753
01:16:27,692 --> 01:16:31,140
But that means
we'll always be strangers.

754
01:16:31,253 --> 01:16:33,415
No, not really.

755
01:16:35,253 --> 01:16:38,178
- Only small parts of us.
- The bad parts.

756
01:16:39,294 --> 01:16:42,025
No, I think it's good
to have a few secrets.

757
01:16:44,414 --> 01:16:46,304
Do you?

758
01:16:49,495 --> 01:16:51,259
That way, in 50 years' time,

759
01:16:51,375 --> 01:16:54,982
we'll still be able
to surprise each other.

760
01:16:55,936 --> 01:16:57,540
Perhaps you're right.

761
01:17:04,056 --> 01:17:05,980
I love you, Piglet.

762
01:17:37,701 --> 01:17:40,830
- What's the matter?
- You must've been dreaming.

763
01:17:40,941 --> 01:17:42,750
When you saw someone with Devlin.

764
01:17:42,861 --> 01:17:44,751
You were so drunk.

765
01:17:44,862 --> 01:17:48,344
I looked in here
and you were absolutely sozzled.

766
01:17:48,463 --> 01:17:52,149
- But it was so real.
- Dreams always are.

767
01:17:52,902 --> 01:17:55,429
The other two swear it wasn't them

768
01:17:55,543 --> 01:17:57,750
and you know how they like to boast.

769
01:17:59,064 --> 01:18:01,305
Do you still like him?

770
01:18:02,504 --> 01:18:07,226
- I suppose so.
- You should go in and see him, then.

771
01:18:07,344 --> 01:18:08,471
NOW?

772
01:18:08,585 --> 01:18:12,670
That's what your dream
was telling you.

773
01:18:14,025 --> 01:18:17,154
Here, put this on.

774
01:18:17,265 --> 01:18:20,315
- But it's your wedding ring.
- It's always brought me luck.

775
01:18:20,426 --> 01:18:22,873
- Has it?
- Always.

776
01:18:22,987 --> 01:18:24,750
Wear these.

777
01:18:27,787 --> 01:18:29,711
Try some of this.

778
01:18:34,988 --> 01:18:37,673
We'll have to fix your hair.

779
01:18:52,230 --> 01:18:53,960
Good luck.

780
01:22:01,134 --> 01:22:03,865
I want to wake up now.

781
01:22:17,215 --> 01:22:21,062
- What? It was night...
- You were shouting.

782
01:22:21,176 --> 01:22:23,827
Really loudly.
I heard you from the garden.

783
01:22:23,936 --> 01:22:27,737
But I wanted to tell you about
last night. Oh, it was wonderful.

784
01:22:27,857 --> 01:22:31,100
I mean, I didn't do everything
with him because...

785
01:22:31,217 --> 01:22:33,823
I don't think
he's good enough for me but...

786
01:22:33,937 --> 01:22:37,260
oh, he did some things
which were just...

787
01:22:39,538 --> 01:22:40,949
Gosh!

788
01:22:49,340 --> 01:22:52,184
How dare you use her
without permission?

789
01:22:52,300 --> 01:22:56,829
- I don't need permission.
- It infers that she modelled!

790
01:22:57,980 --> 01:23:00,143
You cannot just put
someone in your painting!

791
01:23:00,261 --> 01:23:03,743
It's totally compromising.
She'll be outraged. I'm outraged!

792
01:23:03,862 --> 01:23:07,230
- Perhaps we ought to ask her.
- I don't need to. If she wanted...

793
01:23:07,342 --> 01:23:09,629
Anthony? What's the matter?

794
01:23:09,742 --> 01:23:12,712
Mr Lindsay has put you
in his latest painting.

795
01:23:14,063 --> 01:23:16,669
He has to paint over you
or we'll take legal action.

796
01:23:16,783 --> 01:23:20,788
He can turn you into someone else.
You'd better have a look.

797
01:23:45,786 --> 01:23:47,789
Well?

798
01:24:10,309 --> 01:24:12,881
It's a good likeness.

799
01:24:49,914 --> 01:24:54,682
Devlin, better get back
to work. Catch.

800
01:26:00,283 --> 01:26:02,889
They're asleep.

801
01:26:03,003 --> 01:26:04,926
For goodness sake!

802
01:26:09,444 --> 01:26:10,810
We'll be arrested.

803
01:26:14,605 --> 01:26:17,176
We'll be excommunicated.

